fields.name: Insane in the Brain: Cypress Hill
fields.projectCopy: The unique, smoke-filled story of the trailblazing hip-hop group who built a musical movement rooted in true authenticity. We leaned into that idea with a singular image and an illustrated mark pulled from the groups West Coast history to create an original, everlasting legacy still burning bright today.

fields.name: Flatbush Misdemeanors
fields.projectCopy: Kevin and Dan are two best friends in their twenties who are trying to balance their careers, relationships, and life in Flatbush, Brooklyn. The show combines cynical humor and raw honesty to delve into themes of identity, family, and friendship in a neighborhood that is constantly changing, sometimes so fast you feel youâ€™re sitting on the edge.

fields.name: Love and Mercy
fields.projectCopy: Letâ€™s be honest, the last few years have been a lot. The cumulative exhaustion and unease about what would happen next were pervasive. We all felt the same way and there was no sense in hiding it.

fields.name: Crime Scene
fields.projectCopy: The new season of the Joe Berlinger series, directed by Jessica Dimmock, delves into "The Texas Killing Fields," a place with a troubling history of young girls who have gone missing and been found dead for the past 40 years. The in-episode graphics and main title sequence we created were stripped down to their essentials, mirroring the harsh Texas sun and wind.

fields.name: The Affair
fields.projectCopy: At once deeply observed and intriguingly elusive, The Affair explores the emotional effects of an extramarital relationship. Told from the perspectives of the four main characters, each with their own unique memory biases, the show explores the complexities of desire and longing. The key art focuses not on the intricate web of narratives but on the powerful idea that wanting and needing something can be two vastly different things.

fields.name: Freedom
fields.projectCopy: Focusing on the formative period in the late GrammyÂ®â€¯Award winnerâ€™s life and career, leading up to and following the making of his acclaimed, best-selling album â€œListen Without Prejudice Vol. 1â€ and his subsequent, infamous High Court battle with his record label that followed. The film features Georgeâ€™s unheard perspective on changing the music industry as well as incredible, unseen archival and private footage culminating in a vibrantly beautiful portrait of the artist.

fields.name: Supreme Team
fields.projectCopy: The three-part limited series, directed by Nasir "Nas" Jones and Peter J Scalettar, explores the infamous Queens, New York gang, through the eyes of its two leaders, Kenneth "Supreme" McGriff and Gerald "Prince" Miller, and their families. The myth they created during the 80s and 90s in New York streets was larger than life and still resonates in the city today.

fields.name: The Circus
fields.projectCopy: Hosts John Heilemann, Mark McKinnon and Jennifer Palmieri go beyond the headlines to examine the politics impacting us all. The series has always showcased that fine line between disaster and promise of the great American political experiment. Are we a country veering off the edge or making another grand leap forward?

fields.name: 2nd Chance
fields.projectCopy: A documentary chronicling the life of Richard Davis, the man who invented the concealable bulletproof vest - shooting himself 196 times in the course of his career to prove the effectiveness of his vests. Yup. And we salute his commitment to putting a target on his own chest.

fields.name: The Motel
fields.projectCopy: Thirteen-year-old Ernest Chin lives and works at a sleazy hourly-rate motel on a strip of desolate suburban bi-way. Misunderstood by his family and blindly careening into puberty, Ernest befriends Sam Kim, a self-destructive yet charismatic Korean man who has checked in. Sam teaches the fatherless boy all the rites of manhood. And what better way to illustrate the trials and tribulations of a young Ernest but through the panels of a comic.

fields.name: Billions
fields.projectCopy: A vanitas (Latin for 'vanity') is a symbolic work of art, usually a still life, showing the transience of life, the futility of pleasure, and the certainty of death, often contrasting symbols of wealth and symbols of ephemerality and death. Itâ€™s also Latin for â€œover-the-top war between hedge fund king Bobby â€˜Axeâ€™ Axelrod and ruthless U.S. Attorney Chuck Rhoadesâ€. Self-preservation is the name of the game this season, which is hard to do when thereâ€™s no one at the table you can trust.

fields.name: Murder in Big Horn
fields.projectCopy: Directors Razelle Benally and Matthew Galkin craft a powerful portrait of tribal members and their communities within Big Horn County, Montana battling an epidemic of Missing and Murdered Indigenous Women that has been prevalent since colonization. The three-part docuseries examines the circumstances surrounding many of these cases, told through the perspectives of local law enforcement officers, Native families, and Native journalists.

fields.name: The Chi
fields.projectCopy: Itâ€™s not a secret that the South Side of Chicago can be dangerous, and the smallest and simplest of decisions can have life or death consequences for the residents. But EmmyÂ® winner Lena Waithe, creator of the series, also shows us the beauty in all of the stories that make up a real placeâ€“not just the news clips. This is really a vibrant canvas tellig the story of a group of residents who become linked by coincidence but bonded by the need for connection and redemption.

fields.name: I'm Dying Up Here
fields.projectCopy: Is it worth it? Is facing death every night on that stage worth all the crap that comes with even a glimmer of success? Exploring the famed Los Angeles stand-up scene of the 1970s as a group of comedy hopefuls stand alone on stage, "dying" for fame, fortune and -- if they're lucky -- a shot on Johnny Carson's show. We opted for something darkly funny, with an emphasis on the dark, while also focusing in on each comicâ€™s own personal reaction to that struggle looming above them.

fields.name: Kidding
fields.projectCopy: Jim Carrey is Mr. Pickles, an icon of childrenâ€™s television to Americaâ€™s impressionable young minds and the parents who grew up with him. We realized that this is the story of a kind man in cruel world, facing a slow leak of his own sanity and that no fairy tale, fable or puppet could guide him through everyheartbreak no matter how much he wished for that helping hand to carry him away.

fields.name: Moonbase 8
fields.projectCopy:
Fred Armisen, Tim Heidecker and John C. Reilly? Yes, please. 

Theyâ€™re three astronauts stationed at NASA's Moon Base Simulator in a remote part of the Arizona desert. While working vigorously to qualify for their first lunar mission, they encounter obstacles like loneliness, self-doubt and their own total  incompetence. Working with the uber talented Akiko Stehrenberger on this new comedy series to visualize, in spite of it all, that they remain determined to prove they have the right stuff to possibly reach the moon.

fields.name: In the Darkness of Being
fields.projectCopy: The short film of a dream-induced journey into a young manâ€™s search for acceptance and a personal journey from filmmaker Joey Ohls.

fields.name: Escape from Dannemora
fields.projectCopy: This limited series is based on the stranger-than-fiction account of a prison break in upstate New York in the summer of 2015 that spawned a massive manhunt for two convicted murderers. Ben Stiller crafted a psychological throwback to 1970â€™s thrillers using real places to real people to tell this story. With that direction, we used images from the series to highlight moments that were evocative of the realism that was at the heart of this true story.

fields.name: The Loudest Voice
fields.projectCopy: Roger Ailes looms large; over Fox news and the empire he built, over all media and the landscape within which we understand news, and even over the whole country. The series focused on defining events in Ailesâ€™ life, including his experiences with world leaders that gave birth to his political career, and the sexual harassment accusations and settlements that brought his Fox News reign to an end. But, to understand the events that led to Americaâ€™s fractured states, one must understand Ailes.

fields.name: Motel
fields.projectCopy: From photographer Eric Ogden comes a short film about sibling rivalry and intimacy, and the seismic waves mental illness can affect on others, MOTEL plumbs these very real emotional depths and at the same time questions if an outside â€œeventâ€ has happened, framed within the genre conventions of psychological horror.

fields.name: City of Angels
fields.projectCopy: 1938 Los Angeles is a time and place deeply infused with social and political tension. When a grisly murder shocks the city two detectives become embroiled in the dark, rich history of Los Angeles. Mixing folklore, the supernatural, the Third Reich and the rise of radio evangelism the world is on the verge of burning down around them.

fields.name: Happyish
fields.projectCopy: Thom Payne is a 44 year-old ad man whose world is thrown into disarray when his 25 year-old "wunderkind" boss arrives, saying things like "digital", "social" and "viral." Is he in need of a "rebranding", or does he just have a "low joy ceiling"? Originally, the cloud was a middle-finger but maybe pursuing happiness is a fool's errand? Either way, Thom lives in a  ludicrous world learning to embrace the end of everything he new and trying to settle for just happy-ish.

fields.name: White Famous
fields.projectCopy: Talented young comic Floyd Mooney is on the rise, which forces him to navigate the treacherous waters of maintaining his credibility while crossing over into becoming "white famous." We wanted to take the simple design and add a bespoke hand-made typography that brought the words around Floyd to life.

fields.name: Shameless
fields.projectCopy: Season 10 of sees Frank attempting to maintain his newfound sobriety, while Fiona struggles to start a new life in Seattle. But really, this is Shameless and the Gallaghers worst enemy areâ€¦the Gallaghers. Thereâ€™s a little bit of wild pro-wrestling in every moment, we just brought that feeling to life.

fields.name: Billions
fields.projectCopy: Season 5 of Billions is full of billainaires, power struggles, and rich people doing rich things all bathed in rich golden light. But, as expected, things get complicated with the entrance of a cunning new player and the return of some old enemies. The trick is really getting all those eyelines to work with the right amount of cool suspicion.

fields.name: Who is America?
fields.projectCopy: Who is a Republican? Who is a Democrat?? Who is America??? Out of our own national anxiety and finger-pointing comes Sacha Baron Cohen with all of the answers (maybe). Part of the visual campaign was dependant not only on taking a peek at the anticipation of what Sacha Baron Cohens absurdist humor might channel next but also what uncomfortable truths a new cast of characters might reveal.

fields.name: The Comedy Store
fields.projectCopy: The limited series takes viewers behind the scenes of the legendary comedy club, through a blend of interviews, archive footage, and reenactments. The show explores the rich history of the club, showcasing its outrageous comedy, nostalgia, and the vivid stories of the comedians who made it famous. The result is a vintage piece of art that celebrates the art of making people laugh.

fields.projectCopy: FPO Copy. The in-episode graphics and main title sequence we created were stripped down to their essentials, mirroring the harsh Texas sun and wind.
